CHOLERA - ANGOLA
****************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Wed, 12 Nov 1997
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Media reports

According to media reports, the Luanda Bureau of Health posted a public
notice on November 10, 1997 reporting five cases of cholera in the Angolan
capital city. These are the first cases in the capital this year.
Residents have been urged to boil drinking water and to remove garbage that
has collected in city streets.
--
Dorothy Preslar
ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[It appears that ProMED-mail has received few, if any prior reports of
cholera outbreaks in Angola. We would appreciate further information as to
the severity of this outbreak, updates on the current situation and a
historical perspective. - Mod.ES]
